<PB REF="2">
<HEAD>THE TRANSLATOR TO THE READER.</HEAD>
<P>THE following Di&s;cour&s;e having been deliver'd in a <HI>Learned Lan|guage,</HI> to a <HI>Learned</HI> and <HI>Venerable Auditory,</HI> and upon a <HI>&s;olemn Occa&s;ion,</HI> many well-di&s;po&s;ed Per&s;ons, who are not acquainted with the <HI>Latin</HI> Tongue, may be curious of knowing what is contained in it. For the Satisfaction of The&s;e Men, and for the &s;ake of tho&s;e two mo&s;t de&s;ira|ble Things, which are here treated of, <HI>Peace</HI> and <HI>Edification,</HI> I have ventur'd to hand it into the World in our Mother-Tongue.</P>
